46    /**
47    * A class or an interface type. <br/><code>Object</code> <br/><code>HashMap&lt;String, String></code>
48    * <br/><code>java.util.Punchcard</code>
49    * <p>
50    * <p>Note that the syntax is ambiguous here, and JavaParser does not know what is to the left of the class. It assumes
51    * cases like <code>Map.Entry</code> where Map is the scope of Entry. In <code>java.util.Punchcard</code>, it will not
52    * recognize that java and util are parts of the package name. Instead, it will set util as the scope of Punchcard, as a
